:: ContinueDreamNatasha {"position":"400,2100","size":"100,100"}
{(set: $dreamLevel to $dreamLevel + 1)}
You ignore the alarm.

The creature surfaces fully now, impossibly close. Its body is a contradiction, solid and liquid, here and there, one creature and many.

It doesn't attack. Instead, it mirrors your movements, tilting its head when you tilt yours, stepping when you step.

You begin to understand Natasha's schizophrenia, not as random chaos, but as a pattern that makes sense only to itself. The voices aren't random, they're trying to warn her. The paranoia isn't baseless, her mind truly believes threats lurk everywhere.

She's not broken. She's adapted to a reality that doesn't exist.



[[(Explore the zone further)->ContinueDreamNatasha2]]

[[(WAKE UP)->WakeUpNatasha]]


:: ContinueDreamNatasha2 {"position":"400,2300","size":"100,100"}
{(set: $dreamLevel to $dreamLevel + 2)}

The door remains, but the swamp transforms around it.

The crystalline water turns opaque, then transparent again, cycling between states. The creature multiplies, becoming two, five, dozens, all moving in perfect synchronization.

They speak now, all with the same voice: Natasha's voice.

"They know I'm different."
"They know I see things."
"They know I know."

{(if: $studiedReflection is true)
[
You understand now, she's not afraid of being watched. She's afraid of what they'll do when they confirm what they already suspect, that she's not like them, that her reality is fundamentally different.
]}

The creatures circle you, not threatening, just... present. Always present. Never letting you forget you're being observed.

The swamp whispers a truth: You can't hide from watchers who live inside your own perception.

One creature lunges forward suddenly, wrapping around you, pulling you under the crystalline water.

[[(You wake up)->WakeUpNatasha]]


:: ContinueDreamTheo {"position":"1300,1900","size":"100,100"}
