:: ContinueDreamTheo2 {"position":"1300,2100","size":"100,100"}
{(set: $dreamLevel to $dreamLevel + 2)}

The door remains, but the world shifts around it.
The chessboard bends, squares stretching unevenly. Pieces change roles mid-move, no longer following their own rules.

Equations fill the sky, writing and erasing themselves.

He understands systems perfectly.
But human emotions refuse structure.

He could never fully read them.
He could never solve them.

{(if:  $studiedQueen is true)
[
You can perfectly see why she left
]}

The board falls silent.

The dream is watching you. A rook behaves like a real horse and begins to run until it reaches you and tackles you.

[[(You wake up)->WakeUpTheo]]


