[<img src="https://media.gettyimages.com/id/2113459966/video/eerie-twilight-in-prehistoric-jungle.jpg?s=640x640&k=20&c=lhUzxbU-eW7AFFsQP3S48l_v9pXd1V3PH6cU5CDDWTM=" width="600px" height="500px">]

The world around you is darkness. A thick, humid darkness that presses against your skin like wet fabric.

You're standing in shallow water, ankle-deep. It's crystal clear, impossibly so, you can see every grain of sand beneath the surface, every tiny particle suspended in the liquid.

But beyond the water, you can barely see anything. The night swallows everything.

Twisted trees rise from the swamp like skeletal fingers, their branches reaching but going nowhere. The air smells of rot and flowers at once.

{(if: $askedMother is true)
[
