You feel eyes on you, multiple sets, unblinking.

The water ripples though nothing touched it.
]
(if: $askedMother is false)
[
The swamp is eerily quiet. No insects, no frogs, no life sounds at all.

Just the gentle lap of crystalline water against your legs.

The silence feels deliberate, maintained.
]}


[[(Wade through the swamp)->SwampPath]]

{(if: $askedMother is true)
[
[[(Follow the ripples)->FollowCreature]]
]}


:: ObserveCreature {"position":"500,1500","size":"100,100"}
{
(set: $studiedReflection to true)
}
You watch carefully, staying still in the water.

The creature moves in patterns, circular, obsessive. It's hunting but also hiding, seeking but also fleeing.

You realize, it's afraid of something in the swamp too.

It keeps looking at the darkness beyond the trees, as if watching for a greater threat. Whatever Natasha fears, this creature fears something more.

You understand now, this creature isn't the source of her paranoia. It's a symptom. A manifestation of her need to see threats before they see her.

She created a monster to watch for worse monsters.

The creature slowly sinks into the water, only the ripples remain, moving in concentric circles.



[[(Follow the current)->CreatureCircle]]


